# Expense Tracker - Implementation Plan

## Project Overview
A complete expense tracking web application for B.Tech minor project submission.

## Files to Create (Max 8 files)
1. **index.html** - Main application structure with forms and display areas
2. **style.css** - Modern, professional styling with responsive design
3. **script.js** - Core JavaScript logic for transactions, calculations, and UI
4. **chart.js** - Simple chart visualization for expense categories

## Features Implementation
### Core Features (MVP)
- ✅ Add income transactions with amount, category, description, date
- ✅ Add expense transactions with amount, category, description, date
- ✅ Display current balance (total income - total expenses)
- ✅ Show transaction history list
- ✅ Delete transactions
- ✅ Filter by transaction type (all/income/expense)
- ✅ Category-wise breakdown
- ✅ Data persistence using localStorage
- ✅ Responsive mobile-first design

### Categories
**Income:** Salary, Freelance, Investment, Gift, Other
**Expense:** Food, Transport, Shopping, Bills, Entertainment, Health, Education, Other

## Technical Stack
- HTML5 for structure
- CSS3 for styling (gradients, animations, flexbox/grid)
- Vanilla JavaScript for logic
- localStorage for data persistence
- No external dependencies

## File Relationships
- index.html imports style.css and script.js
- script.js handles all business logic and DOM manipulation
- chart.js creates visual representation of data
- All data stored in browser's localStorage